      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:57:77",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/57/1169",
      "text": [
        " «لاَ وَ لَكِنْ يُؤَذِّنُ وَ يُقِيمُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1169 - Ammar Al-Sabati narrated that he asked Imam (as) about a man who gives the adhan (call to prayer) and iqamah (call to commence the prayer) intending to pray alone. Then another person arrives and asks to pray in congregation. He asked whether they may use the same adhan and iqamah.\nImam (as) replied: \"No, rather he should give the adhan and iqamah again.\""
        ]
      }
    },
